september where were you what were you doing when you heard of the terrorist attack on the u s someone has an obcession with thumbs down to be doing so on this question get real grow up i was in the shower i live on the west coast and i wasn't working that day pretty sure it was a weekday though i slept through the actual time of attack since that was am our time my ex boyfriend and i got up around our time i got in the shower he went out to eat breakfast turned on the tv and i will never forget him coming into the bathroom and saying we have been attacked we have been attacked i was like what in the world are you talking about what does that even mean what has been attacked who attacked us he just left and went back to the tv i got out of the shower came out soaking wet in a towel took one look at the replaying of the towers being hit by a plane literally sunk to my knees tears filled my eyes and all i could say was i don't know where my parents are he said what aren't they in pa i said i don't know i know that they were taking a trip to st john's and i thought it was around that time i didn't know where they were i didn't know what flights were coming from where i got up and called they weren't leaving or supposed to leave for their trip for another weeks and at that point they weren't even sure they were going to go i walked out onto the deck of the apartment top floor i looked in the sky not a single plane was flying and we lived close to the airport so flights were always overhead above us it was eerily quiet the rest of the day was a haze an absolute haze i remember crying uncontrollably for weeks on end in sadness for all thos innocent people if you want to attack my military go ahead but don't kill a bunch of stockbrokers insurance salesman office assitants seriously the attacks made me angry sad miserable i think i cried every night for those families for weeks even now when i think about it it makes me cry it makes me feel ill and it makes me want to find whomever is responsible and spit in their face ignorance kills those people were simply doing working at their desks they didn't control the country they weren't arranging coups in anyone's country they weren't directing nuclear missles at some country's government they worked in an office they were sons mothers fathers brothers sisters aunts uncles friends family and i will remember it always always we truly will never forget Knots Landing Episodes of Lost (Season 1) EastEnders Planning and execution of the September 11, 2001 attacks Piccolo Junior Saga Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Humphrey Bogart The Shining (film) Kodocha Sin City Oplan Bojinka Pitaten One Piece minor characters Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Eddie Guerrero Cindy Sheehan The Wizard of Oz (1939 film) Days of our Lives The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Social rule The Amber Spyglass The X-Files (season 1) September 11, 2001 attacks timeline for the day of the attacks Phoebe Buffay Fancy Crane StarCraft: Uprising Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Rais massacre Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Ron Weasley Milton H. Erickson The Inside One Tree Hill (TV series) Avenue Q Big Brother (USA TV series) World Trade Center John the Baptist Megan Griffin Pan Am Flight 103 Theory of conduct The Ashlee Simpson Show About a Boy 2004 Republican National Convention Neighbours W.I.T.C.H. Sami Brady Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories Blonde on Blonde Tenshinhan Highway 61 Revisited The Lovely Bones The Catcher in the Rye Airport The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy The Family from One End Street Ziad Jarrah Blood (computer game) Poker jargon Cliff Richard Charles Graner Night (book) The Death Gate Cycle Mojave people Empire Burlesque USS Waters (DD-115) Paul Is Dead Characters of Naruto Tupac Shakur YuYu Hakusho The Marshall Mathers LP Homer Simpson Married... with Children Hey Jude The Emancipation of Mimi A Canticle for Leibowitz King Piccolo Saga Series 